{{Advert|date=May 2010}} '''Providence Christian Academy''' is a multi-denominational, independent school offering classes from Kindergarten to 12 and is located in [[Lilburn, Georgia]]. Founded in 1991, Providence has graduated over 1200 students.
==Today == Providence features a college preparatory curriculum with Honors courses and ten AP courses. The enrollment for 2011 is 668. Providence also accepts international students. The campus is initiating iPads into the curriculum in 2011. All students grades 7-12 will receive an iPad and teachers will use them as a teaching tool.
The school sports teams go by the name "Stars." Providence has produced four state championship teams: 1999 and 2007 Girls Soccer (Class AA/A), 2000 Fast Pitch Softball (Class AA), and 2009 Gymnastics (Class A).
== History== The school opened on September 6, 1991 with 354 students in grades K-12. The original building was a one-building facility which has developed into a campus encompassing 2 buildings and 46 acres. This includes separate facilities for High School, Elementary, Gymnasiums, and Athletic Fields.
From earning accreditation by the Georgia Accrediting Commission, dual accreditation with the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools/Council on Accreditation and School Improvement (SACS/CASI) and the Association of Christian School International (ACSI) Providence continues to provide a college prep curriculum with over 1200 graduates.
== Mission== The mission of Providence Christian Academy is to provide excellence in Christ-centered education as an extension of the Christian home.
